---
description: Accessibility requirements for pages and components
globs: app/**/*.js,components/**/*.js
---

Target WCAG 2.1 AA (see `docs/TESTING.md` for the full accessibility testing
plan and tooling) — this is a public nonprofit site, not a demo, and
accessibility is part of the mission, not an afterthought.

- Every `<Image>`/`<img>` needs meaningful `alt` text; use `alt=""` only for
  purely decorative images.
- Interactive elements — the nav dropdown, carousel prev/next/dot controls,
  mobile menu toggle — must be reachable and operable by keyboard, not just
  mouse/touch. Match the existing patterns in `components/Header.js` and
  `components/HeroCarousel.js` (real `<button>` elements with `aria-label`s,
  not clickable `<div>`s).
- Check new color combinations against WCAG AA contrast (4.5:1 for normal
  text, 3:1 for large text) before using them, especially text over the
  brand colors defined in `app/globals.css`.
- Don't remove a focus outline (`focus:outline-none` etc.) without providing
  a visible replacement (e.g. `focus:ring-2`).
- Use semantic HTML (`<nav>`, `<button>`, `<h1>`–`<h3>` in order, `<ul>`/`<li>`
  for lists) over generic `<div>`s wherever the element's actual role
  matches — screen readers depend on this.
